<hl>
<seg id=1> China to Speed Up Development of Talent Marketing System </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News Agency, Beijing, September 1st. The Organization Department and Personnel Department of the central committee of CPC (Communist Party of China) recently announced a notice to develop an enhanced human resources market in China, thereby creating a system of marketing the abilities of talented persons. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> It was pointed out in the notice that the general objectives of the job market development are: To create a system that allows realization of personal independence in choosing profession; To create a market that regulates the supply, to perfect social service; To create a market that plays a fundamental role in the installment of human resources under national control. </seg>
<seg id=4> The aims of the recent human resources market development are: To establish the keynote policies and laws that human resources market circulation demand in 2-3 years.  To universally establish a human resources market in big and middle sized cities.  To establish and develop the regional human resources information networks.  To support the development of professional human resources markets as well as to establish regional human resource markets. </seg>
<seg id=5> By the year 2000 it is anticipated to set up countrywide a human resources market system with comprehensive functions, healthy mechanism, complete laws and regulations, timely guide and full-range service. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Department of Organization and the Department of Personnel of the Central Committee of CPC required organizational and personnel departments at all levels to enhance the construction and management of human resources market.  In addition, establish the overall layout and practices, make use of regional advantages and adapt to meet regional needs, and gradually establish a perfect system of marketing talent. </seg>
</p>
